Suedehead; The Best Of - Morrissey [1997]

Suedehead: The Best of Morrissey is a compilation album by Morrissey containing material released during his EMI period. It was released on September 8, 1997.Material ranges from 1988's Viva Hate to his 1994's Vauxhall and I album, also containing his 1995 single "Sunny". Although Suedehead predominantly contains singles, it also has several rarities including a cover of "That's Entertainment" by The Jam and the complete version of "Interlude", a duet with Siouxsie Sioux.
